With 64 days to the 2019 Presidential Election, Nigerians will today, Friday, via live television and social media platforms, catch a glimpse of the crossfire between vice presidential candidates of some of the leading political parties in the election as Vice President Yemi Osinbajo of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Peter Obi of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), among others clash in a debate. The debate, which was organised by the Nigerian Election Debate Group (NEDG) and the Broadcasting Organisations of Nigeria (BON) among the vice presidential candidates of some of the parties fielding candidates at next year’s general election, will hold by 7pm at the Congress Hall of the Transcorp Hilton Hotel in Abuja. The VPs’ debate will be shown live on all BON stations like NTA, Channels TV, AIT, Silverbird TV, among others, with Nigerians expected to also follow it live on social media platforms with hashtags like #2019debate, #2019election and on Twitter page https://twitter.com/NaijaDecides19/with_replies. Other contestants expected at the debate are Kingsley Moghalu’s running mate, Umma Getso of the Young Progressive Party (YPP), Dr Oby Ezekwesili’s running mate, Alhaji Abdulganiyu Galadima of the Allied Congress Party of Nigeria (ACPN) and Fela Durotoye’s running mate, Khadijah Abdullahi-Iya of the Alliance for New Nigeria (ANN). According to BON Chairman, John Momoh, the Vice Presidential debate will be streamed live on Facebook, YouTube and Twitter. The debate among leading Presidential candidates, also being organised by NEDG/BON, will hold in January 19 2019 at the same venue.